	]a
	" - A different way to reach the bottom of this ladder in 4-2.  It seems faster, but is actually slower because there's no way to get onto that wall without wasting time.  Sure looks neat, though. =)
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://www.filespace.org/PunchRockgroin/WallNormalJump.fcm rel=nofollow 
		"http://www.filespace.org/PunchRockgroin/WallNormalJump.fcm
	]a
	" - This one's pretty simple, only works on certain walls.  Again, it looks fast but is actually slower than walljumping; this is due to the amount of time wasted as you descend from the jumps.  However, if anyone were to try a legit glitched speedrun of this game, this is actually a very useful trick...it's only a few frames slower than walljumping and is quite easy to perform.
	$LF
